{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858231922,"sessionID":"ses_2869a4295ffeIw1uChU90fAQAt","part":{"id":"prt_d7966278b001DKIWpPoMWKjJuS","messageID":"msg_d79660693001cOUkeVBz4EOrYL","sessionID":"ses_2869a4295ffeIw1uChU90fAQAt","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-35a821b8422d42beba40c02a4b3b8eb8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Implementation Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module**: `pkg/router`\n4: **Language**: Go\n5: **Size**: M\n6: **Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n7: \n8: ## Task Breakdown\n9: \n10: ### Task 1: Fix isNotFoundError implementation in jwt.go\n11: - [ ] Update `isNotFoundError()` function in `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n12: - [ ] Import `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` package\n13: - [ ] Check error using `errors.IsNotFound(err)` instead of hardcoded false\n14: - [ ] Add test case for Secret not found scenario\n15: - [ ] Add test case for other Kubernetes API errors\n16: \n17: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTSecretNotFound` to verify error detection works correctly\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ### Task 2: Implement JWT authentication middleware\n22: - [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go` file\n23: - [ ] Implement `jwtAuthMiddleware()` function accepting *JWTManager parameter\n24: - [ ] Extract Authorization header from request\n25: - [ ] Validate Bearer scheme in Authorization header\n26: - [ ] Call JWTManager.ValidateToken() with extracted token\n27: - [ ] Store session_id in Gin context on successful validation\n28: - [ ] Return 401 Unauthorized with structured error on validation failure\n29: - [ ] Add correlation ID logging for authentication failures\n30: - [ ] Handle missing Authorization header with 401 Unauthorized\n31: - [ ] Handle invalid token format with 401 Unauthorized\n32: - [ ] Handle expired tokens with appropriate error message\n33: \n34: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTMiddleware` to verify middleware behavior\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ### Task 3: Add JWT-specific error definitions\n39: - [ ] Update `pkg/router/errors.go`\n40: - [ ] Define JWT error constants:\n41:   - [ ] `ErrJWTValidationFailed` = \"JWT_VALIDATION_FAILED\"\n42:   - [ ] `ErrJWTTokenExpired` = \"JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED\"\n43:   - [ ] `ErrJWTTokenInvalid` = \"JWT_TOKEN_INVALID\"\n44:   - [ ] `ErrJWTTokenMissing` = \"JWT_TOKEN_MISSING\"\n45:   - [ ] `ErrJWTSigningFailed` = \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n46: - [ ] Define `JWTValidationError` struct implementing HTTPError interface\n47: - [ ] Implement Error() method returning detailed but safe error message\n48: - [ ] Implement HTTPStatusCode() method returning 401\n49: - [ ] Implement ErrorCode() method returning appropriate error code\n50: - [ ] Add unit tests for each JWT error type\n51: \n52: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTErrors` to verify error definitions\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ### Task 4: Update session creation to include JWT token generation\n57: - [ ] Update `pkg/router/handlers.go` session creation handlers\n58: - [ ] Add JWT token generation to AgentRuntime session creation response\n59: - [ ] Add JWT token generation to CodeInterpreter session creation response\n60: - [ ] Update response structures to include `token` field\n61: - [ ] Ensure session ID matches between response and JWT claims\n62: - [ ] Handle JWT generation failures gracefully\n63: - [ ] Add logging for successful token generation\n64: - [ ] Add logging for token generation failures\n65: \n66: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionCreationWithToken` to verify token generation\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ### Task 5: Create comprehensive JWT unit tests\n71: - [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` file\n72: - [ ] Implement `TestNewJWTManager_Success` test\n73: - [ ] Implement `TestNewJWTManager_NilClientset` test\n74: - [ ] Implement `TestNewJWTManager_DefaultNamespace` test\n75: - [ ] Implement `TestGenerateToken_Success` test\n76: - [ [ ] Implement `TestGenerateToken_NoPrivateKey` test\n77: - [ ] Implement `TestValidateToken_Success` test\n78: - [ ] Implement `TestValidateToken_ExpiredToken` test\n79: - [ ] Implement `TestValidateToken_InvalidSignature` test\n80: - [ ] Implement `TestValidateToken_NoPublicKey` test\n81: - [ ] Implement `TestGenerateRSAKeyPair` test\n82: - [ ] Implement `TestStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret_CreateNew` test (mock Kubernetes)\n83: - [ ] Implement `TestStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret_LoadExisting` test (mock Kubernetes)\n84: - [ ] Implement `TestLoadKeysFromSecret_MissingPrivateKey` test\n85: - [ ] Implement `TestLoadKeysFromSecret_MissingPublicKey` test\n86: - [ ] Implement `TestParsePrivateKeyPEM_Success` test\n87: - [ ] Implement `TestParsePrivateKeyPEM_InvalidFormat` test\n88: - [ ] Implement `TestParsePublicKeyPEM_Success` test\n89: - [ ] Implement `TestParsePublicKeyPEM_InvalidFormat` test\n90: - [ ] Implement `TestJWTClaimsSerialization` test\n91: \n92: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWT` to verify all JWT unit tests pass\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ### Task 6: Create JWT middleware tests\n97: - [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_ValidToken` test\n98: - [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_MissingToken` test\n99: - [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_InvalidToken` test\n100: - [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_ExpiredToken` test\n101: - [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_WrongScheme` test\n102: - [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_SessionIDInContext` test\n103: - [ ] Implement `TestJWTAuthMiddleware_ErrorResponseFormat` test\n104: - [ ] Test correlation ID logging on authentication failures\n105: \n106: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTMiddleware` to verify middleware tests pass\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ### Task 7: Create JWT middleware tests with table-driven approach\n111: - [ ] Implement table-driven test for middleware scenarios\n112: - [ ] Test case: Valid Bearer token → Success\n113: - [ ] Test case: Missing Authorization header → 401\n114: - [ ] Test case: Empty Authorization header → 401\n115: - [ ] Test case: Authorization header without \"Bearer\" → 401\n116: - [ ] Test case: Malformed token string → 401\n117: - [ ] Test case: Expired token → 401 with expiration error\n118: - [ ] Test case: Invalid signature → 401 with validation error\n119: - [ ] Test case: Valid token with session_id → Context set\n120: \n121: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTMiddlewareTableDriven` to verify all scenarios\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Task 8: Implement JWT-related logging enhancements\n126: - [ ] Update `pkg/router/jwt.go` logging statements\n127: - [ ] Add Info level log when keys are loaded from Secret\n128: - [ ] Add Info level log when keys are stored in Secret\n129: - [ ] Add Warning level log when Secret access fails and fallback occurs\n130: - [ ] Add Error level log when key generation fails\n131: - [ ] Update middleware logging for authentication failures\n132: - [ ] Add correlation ID to all JWT-related log entries\n133: - [ ] Ensure no sensitive information (private keys) is logged\n134: \n135: **Verification**: Review log output during test runs to verify appropriate logging levels and messages\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Task 9: Create JWT performance benchmarks\n140: - [ ] Create benchmark functions in `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n141: - [ ] Implement `BenchmarkGenerateToken` to measure token generation speed\n142: - [ ] Implement `BenchmarkValidateToken` to measure token validation speed\n143: - [ ] Implement `BenchmarkGenerateRSAKeyPair` to measure key generation speed\n144: - [ ] Implement `BenchmarkConcurrentTokenGeneration` to test concurrent operations\n145: - [ ] Implement `BenchmarkConcurrentTokenValidation` to test concurrent operations\n146: - [ ] Target: P99 latency for GenerateToken < 10ms\n147: - [ ] Target: P99 latency for ValidateToken < 5ms\n148: \n149: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -bench=BenchmarkJWT -benchmem` to verify performance targets\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ### Task 10: Create JWT security tests\n154: - [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt_security_test.go`\n155: - [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_AlgorithmConfusionAttack` test\n156: - [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_NoneAlgorithmAttack` test\n157: - [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_TokenTampering` test\n158: - [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_ReplayAttack` test\n159: - [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_LongTokenAttack` test\n160: - [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_InvalidBase64Token` test\n161: - [ ] Implement `TestSecurity_MissingRequiredClaims` test\n162: - [ ] Test that middleware prevents algorithm confusion\n163: - [ ] Test that tokens with \"none\" algorithm are rejected\n164: \n165: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSecurityJWT` to verify security measures\n166: \n167: ---\n168: \n169: ### Task 11: Create JWT integration tests\n170: - [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt_integration_test.go`\n171: - [ ] Implement `TestE2E_JWTAuthenticationFlow` test\n172:   - [ ] Create session and verify token is returned\n173:   - [ ] Use token to authenticate subsequent request\n174:   - [ ] Verify middleware accepts valid token\n175:   - [ ] Verify session_id is correctly set in context\n176: - [ ] Implement `TestE2E_JWTTokenExpiration` test\n177:   - [ ] Create session with short expiration\n178:   - [ ] Wait for token to expire\n179:   - [ ] Verify expired token is rejected\n180: - [ ] Implement `TestE2E_JWTPersistenceAcrossRequests` test\n181:   - [ ] Generate token and use in multiple requests\n182:   - [ ] Verify all requests succeed with same token\n183:   - [ ] Verify session_id consistency\n184: \n185: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestIntegrationJWT` to verify end-to-end JWT flow\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Task 12: Update handler tests to include JWT token verification\n190: - [ ] Update `pkg/router/handlers_test.go` session creation tests\n191: - [ ] Add assertions to verify token field in response\n192: - [ ] Add assertions to verify token is valid JWT format\n193: - [ ] Add assertions to verify token can be validated\n194: - [ ] Add assertions to verify session_id in token matches response\n195: - [ ] Test session creation failure when JWT generation fails\n196: - [ ] Test error handling when JWT manager is not initialized\n197: \n198: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandlersWithJWT` to verify handlers work with JWT\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ### Task 13: Add JWT configuration support\n203: - [ ] Update `pkg/router/config.go` if needed for JWT configuration\n204: - [ ] Add environment variable for custom token expiration time (if required)\n205: - [ ] Add environment variable for custom Secret name (if required)\n206: - [ ] Update DefaultConfig() to include JWT-related defaults\n207: - [ ] Update LoadConfig() to read JWT-related environment variables\n208: - [ ] Update Config.Validate() to validate JWT configuration\n209: - [ ] Add tests for JWT configuration loading\n210: \n211: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTConfig` to verify configuration handling\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ### Task 14: Implement key rotation support (optional enhancement)\n216: - [ ] Add key rotation method to JWTManager\n217: - [ ] Implement RotateKeys() method\n218: - [ ] Generate new RSA key pair\n219: - [ ] Update Secret with new keys\n220: - [ ] Support old keys for validation during transition period\n221: - [ ] Add logging for key rotation events\n222: - [ ] Add tests for key rotation functionality\n223: \n224: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTKeyRotation` to verify key rotation works\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ### Task 15: Update API documentation with JWT authentication\n229: - [ ] Update `pkg/router/README.md` with JWT authentication documentation\n230: - [ ] Document JWT token format and claims\n231: - [ ] Document Authorization header format (Bearer scheme)\n232: - [ ] Document token expiration behavior\n233: - [ ] Provide curl examples with JWT authentication\n234: - [ ] Document error responses for JWT failures\n235: - [ ] Add JWT authentication flow diagram\n236: - [ ] Update API endpoint documentation with authentication requirements\n237: \n238: **Verification**: Review documentation for completeness and accuracy\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ### Task 16: Create JWT usage examples\n243: - [ ] Create examples directory if needed\n244: - [ ] Create example demonstrating token generation\n245: - [ ] Create example demonstrating token validation\n246: - [ ] Create example demonstrating authenticated API calls\n247: - [ ] Create example demonstrating error handling for JWT failures\n248: - [ ] Ensure all examples compile and run correctly\n249: \n250: **Verification**: Run all examples to verify they work correctly\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ### Task 17: Add JWT metrics collection\n255: - [ ] Implement metrics in JWTManager or middleware\n256: - [ ] Track successful token validations\n257: - [ ] Track failed token validations\n258: - [ ] Track token generation count\n259: - [ ] Track token validation latency\n260: - [ ] Track authentication failures by error type\n261: - [ ] Export metrics in Prometheus format\n262: - [ ] Add tests for metrics collection\n263: \n264: **Verification**: Verify metrics are exported correctly and contain expected data\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ### Task 18: Implement concurrent safety tests\n269: - [ ] Add race detection to JWT tests\n270: - [ ] Implement `TestConcurrentGenerateToken` test\n271: - [ ] Implement `TestConcurrentValidateToken` test\n272: - [ ] Implement `TestConcurrentMixedOperations` test\n273: - [ ] Run tests with race detector enabled\n274: - [ ] Verify no race conditions detected\n275: \n276: **Verification**: Run `go test -race ./pkg/router -run TestJWTConcurrent` to verify thread safety\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ### Task 19: Add JWT health check endpoint\n281: - [ ] Update health check handlers to include JWT manager status\n282: - [ ] Verify JWT manager is initialized\n283: - [ ] Verify keys are available\n284: - [ ] Return JWT manager health status in /healthz/ready endpoint\n285: - [ ] Add tests for JWT health check\n286: \n287: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTHealthCheck` to verify health check works\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ### Task 20: Final verification and cleanup\n292: - [ ] Run full JWT test suite\n293:   - [ ] `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWT -v` - All JWT tests pass\n294:   - [ ] `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTMiddleware -v` - All middleware tests pass\n295:   - [ ] `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSecurityJWT -v` - All security tests pass\n296: - [ ] Run tests with race detector\n297:   - [ ] `go test -race ./pkg/router -run TestJWT` - No race conditions\n298: - [ ] Run benchmarks\n299:   - [ ] `go test ./pkg/router -bench=BenchmarkJWT` - Performance targets met\n300: - [ ] Run static analysis\n301:   - [ ] `go vet ./pkg/router` - No warnings\n302:   - [ ] `golangci-lint run ./pkg/router` - No linting issues (if available)\n303: - [ ] Verify code coverage\n304:   - [ ] `go test ./pkg/router -coverprofile=coverage.out` - Coverage meets requirements\n305: - [ ] Verify integration tests\n306:   - [ ] `go test ./pkg/router -run TestIntegrationJWT` - All integration tests pass\n307: - [ ] Review code for potential security issues\n308: - [ ] Verify error messages don't expose sensitive information\n309: - [ ] Verify logging doesn't expose private keys or tokens\n310: - [ ] Clean up any temporary test files or mock data\n311: \n312: **Verification**: All verification steps pass with no errors or warnings\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## Summary\n317: \n318: **Total Tasks**: 20\n319: **Estimated Effort**: M (Medium) - 10-15 hours\n320: \n321: ### Key Deliverables\n322: 1. `jwt_middleware.go` - JWT authentication middleware\n323: 2. `jwt_test.go` - Comprehensive JWT unit tests\n324: 3. `jwt_security_test.go` - Security-focused JWT tests\n325: 4. `jwt_integration_test.go` - End-to-end JWT flow tests\n326: 5. Updated `errors.go` - JWT-specific error types\n327: 6. Updated `handlers.go` - Token generation on session creation\n328: 7. Updated `jwt.go` - Bug fixes and enhancements\n329: 8. Enhanced logging for JWT operations\n330: 9. Performance benchmarks for JWT operations\n331: 10. Updated documentation with JWT authentication\n332: \n333: ### Success Criteria\n334: - All tasks completed with tests passing\n335: - Code compiles without errors or warnings\n336: - Test coverage meets quality standards (target: 85%+ for JWT code)\n337: - Performance benchmarks meet requirements (P99 latency targets)\n338: - Security tests demonstrate robustness against common attacks\n339: - Documentation is complete and accurate\n340: - Integration with existing router components works correctly\n341: - No race conditions detected under concurrent load\n342: - Error handling provides clear, safe messages\n343: - Logging provides appropriate visibility without exposing secrets\n344: \n345: ### Dependencies\n346: - Go 1.24+\n347: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` v5.2.0+\n348: - `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` v1.10.0+\n349: - `k8s.io/client-go` v0.34.1+\n350: - `k8s.io/klog/v2` v2.120.0+\n351: - Internal packages: `pkg/router`, `pkg/common/types`, `pkg/api`\n352: \n353: ### Blocked By\n354: - None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n355: \n356: ### Blocks\n357: - AR-009 (Router HTTP 反向代理核心) - Depends on JWT authentication for protected endpoints\n358: - AR-012 (Router session management) - Integration with JWT authentication\n359: - AR-013 (Router error handling) - JWT error handling integration\n360: - Production deployment with JWT authentication enabled\n361: \n362: ### Notes\n363: - JWT tokens use RS256 signing algorithm for security\n364: - Default token expiration: 5 minutes\n365: - Keys are persisted in Kubernetes Secret \"picod-router-identity\"\n366: - Fallback to in-memory keys if Secret access fails\n367: - Token format: `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n368: - Session ID is included in `session_id` claim\n369: - All JWT operations are thread-safe\n370: - Error messages do not expose sensitive information\n371: - Logging uses appropriate levels (Info, Warning, Error)\n\n(End of file - total 371 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `pkg/router`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Fix isNotFoundError implementation in jwt.go\n- [ ] Update `isNotFoundError()` function in `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- [ ] Import `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` package\n- [ ] Check error using `errors.IsNotFound(err)` instead of hardcoded false\n- [ ] Add test case for Secret not found scenario\n- [ ] Add test case for other Kubernetes API errors\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTSecretNotFound` to verify error detection works correctly\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775858231909,"end":1775858231920}}}}
