ication**: Run `go test -race ./pkg/picod -run TestConcurrent` to verify thread safety\n\n---\n\n### Task 35: Update go.mod and ensure package is included\n- [ ] Ensure `pkg/picod` is in the correct location\n- [ ] Update parent `go.mod` if needed\n- [ ] Run `go mod tidy` to ensure all dependencies are resolved\n- [ ] Verify package can be imported\n\n**Verification**: Run `go build ./pkg/picod` to verify package builds\n\n---\n\n### Task 36: Create CLI binary\n- [ ] Build CLI binary: `go build -o picod ./cmd/picod`\n- [ ] Test binary execution\n- [ ] Test all CLI flags\n- [ ] Verify binary works correctly\n\n**Verification**: Run `./picod -help` and `./picod -port 9090` to verify binary works\n\n---\n\n### Task 37: Final verification and cleanup\n- [ ] Run full test suite:\n  - [ ] `go test ./pkg/picod -v` - All unit tests pass\n  - [ ] `go test ./pkg/picod -run TestIntegration -v` - All integration tests pass\n  - [ ] `go test ./pkg/picod -run TestSecurity -v` - All security tests pass\n- [ ] Run tests with race detector:\n  - [ ] `go test -race ./pkg/picod` - No race conditions\n- [ ] Run benchmarks:\n  - [ ] `go test ./pkg/picod -bench=. -benchmem` - Benchmarks run successfully\n- [ ] Run static analysis:\n  - [ ] `go vet ./pkg/picod` - No warnings\n  - [ ] `golangci-lint run ./pkg/picod` - No linting issues (if available)\n- [ ] Verify code coverage:\n  - [ ] `go test ./pkg/picod -coverprofile=coverage.out` - Coverage meets requirements\n- [ ] Verify package builds:\n  - [ ] `go build ./pkg/picod` - Package builds successfully\n  - [ ] `go build ./cmd/picod` - CLI builds successfully\n- [ ] Review code for security issues\n- [ ] Verify error messages don't expose sensitive information\n- [ ] Verify logging doesn't expose secrets\n- [ ] Clean up any temporary test files or mock data\n- [ ] Ensure all constants and types match design specifications\n\n**Verification**: All verification steps pass with no errors or warnings\n\n---\n\n### Task 38: Update documentation\n- [ ] Create `pkg/picod/README.md`:\n  - [ ] Package overview\n  - [ ] Installation instructions\n  - [ ] Configuration reference (environment variables, CLI flags)\n  - [ ] API documentation (all endpoints)\n  - [ ] Usage examples\n  - [ ] Security considerations\n  - [ ] Troubleshooting guide\n- [ ] Add inline code comments for complex logic\n- [ ] Document all exported functions and types\n- [ ] Update CHANGE.md status to Completed\n- [ ] Update delta-spec with implementation notes if needed\n\n**Verification**: Review documentation for completeness and accuracy\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Total Tasks**: 38\n**Estimated Effort**: M (Medium) - 12-18 hours\n\n### Key Deliverables\n1. `pkg/picod/constants.go` - All constants and error messages\n2. `pkg/picod/config.go` - Configuration structures\n3. `pkg/picod/errors.go` - Error types and handling\n4. `pkg/picod/auth.go` - JWT authentication manager\n5. `pkg/picod/execute.go` - Command execution types\n6. `pkg/picod/files.go` - File operation types and path sanitization\n7. `pkg/picod/server.go` - Server initialization and routing\n8. `pkg/picod/handlers.go` - All HTTP request handlers\n9. `pkg/picod/middleware.go` - Authentication middleware\n10. `cmd/picod/main.go` - CLI entry point\n11. `cmd/picod/flags.go` - CLI flag definitions\n12. Comprehensive test suite (unit, integration, security, benchmarks)\n13. Package documentation\n\n### Success Criteria\n- All tasks completed with tests passing\n- Code compiles without errors or warnings\n- Test coverage meets quality standards (target: 85%+)\n- All API endpoints work correctly:\n  - Command execution with timeout and output capture\n  - File upload (multipart and JSON Base64)\n  - File listing\n  - File download\n  - Health check\n- JWT authentication works correctly for all /api/* endpoints\n- Path sanitization prevents workspace escape\n- Error responses follow consistent format\n- Graceful shutdown works correctly\n- Security tests demonstrate robustness\n- No race conditions under concurrent load\n- Performance benchmarks meet requirements\n- CLI binary builds and runs correctly\n- Documentation is complete and accurate\n\n### Dependencies\n- Go 1.24+\n- `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` v1.10.0+\n- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` v5.2.0+\n- `k8s.io/klog/v2` v2.130.1+\n- `github.com/stretchr/testify` v1.9.0+ (Testing)\n\n### Blocked By\n- None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n\n### Blocks\n- AR-009 (Router HTTP 反向代理核心) - Router may integrate with PicoD for code execution\n- AR-011 (Router JWT 认证与签发) - JWT authentication integration\n- Production deployment with PicoD as code execution engine\n\n### Notes\n- PicoD uses RS256 signing algorithm for JWT authentication\n- Public key is loaded from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n- Default port: 8080\n- Default timeout: 60 seconds\n- Maximum request body size: 32 MiB\n- Workspace jail enforced through path sanitization\n- All /api/* endpoints require JWT authentication\n- /health endpoint is publicly accessible\n- File modes default to 0644, maximum 0777\n- Directory mode: 0755\n- Timeout exit code: 124\n- Server supports graceful shutdown\n- ReadHeaderTimeout: 10 seconds\n- Gin runs in ReleaseMode\n- Error messages do not expose sensitive information\n- Logging uses klog with appropriate severity levels","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775858348711,"end":1775858348720}}}}
